						<div class="postbody">We could build a laser SDTV without <em>too</em> much difficulty. Modulating red and blue solid-state laser diodes at the required â‰ˆ3MHz bandwidth is pretty easy; I'm not certain whether the nonlinear optics used by green solid-state lasers pose a problem or not.<br /><br />The horizontal deflection is the only particularly hard part, and I think a high-precision many-sided front-surface mirrored polygonal prism should be workable there.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

